  "summary": "Important: raptor2 security update",
  "details": "Raptor is the RDF Parser Toolkit for Redland that provides a set of standalone RDF parsers, generating triples from RDF/XML or N-Triples.   \n\nSecurity Fix(es):  \n\n  * raptor: integer underflow when normalizing a URI with the turtle parser (CVE-2024-57823)\n\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.\n",
